            <div style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt">&nbsp;</div>
            <div style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt">&nbsp;</div>
            <div style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><strong><u><span style="font-family: Candara; font-size: 11pt">Description / Position Comments: </span></u></strong></div>
            <div style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="font-family: Candara; font-size: 11pt">Automation tester will be specifically responsible for Load &amp; Performance testing, so a background in testing applications using significant user concurrency - especially via the internet is highly desirable of this position.</span></div>
            <div style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt">&nbsp;</div>
            <div style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><strong><u><span style="font-family: Candara; font-size: 11pt">Summary: </span></u></strong></div>
            <ul type="disc" style="margin-top: 0in">
                <li style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="font-family: Candara; font-size: 11pt">Responsible for the planning, coordination and monitoring of automated testing tools and strategies. </span></li>
                <li style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="font-family: Candara; font-size: 11pt">Also creates implements and executes automated test scripts and test cases for software project releases.</span></li>
            </ul>
            <div style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt">&nbsp;</div>
            <div style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><strong><u><span style="font-family: Candara; font-size: 11pt">Essential Duties and Responsibilities: </span></u></strong></div>
            <ul type="disc" style="margin-top: 0in">
                <li style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="font-family: Candara; font-size: 11pt">Develops and maintains master test automation plan for software project releases. </span></li>
                <li style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="font-family: Candara; font-size: 11pt">Manages the overall test automation process per the testing methodology, and ensures the testing methods meet the specifications.</span></li>
                <li style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="font-family: Candara; font-size: 11pt">Specifies, builds, manages and organizes relevant test environments and infrastructure. Uses script checks to verify a healthy test environment.</span></li>
                <li style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="font-family: Candara; font-size: 11pt">Develops, maintains and upgrades automated test scripts, utilities, simulators, data sets and other programmatic test tools required to execute test plans.</span></li>
                <li style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="font-family: Candara; font-size: 11pt">Effectively communicates testing activities and findings in oral and written forms.</span></li>
                <li style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="font-family: Candara; font-size: 11pt">Controls and manages daily test automation activities.</span></li>
                <li style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="font-family: Candara; font-size: 11pt">Provides internal quality assurance.</span></li>
                <li style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="font-family: Candara; font-size: 11pt">Identifies risks and develops mitigation strategies. </span></li>
                <li style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="font-family: Candara; font-size: 11pt">Reports on progress of the test automation process.</span></li>
                <li style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="font-family: Candara; font-size: 11pt">Evaluates the overall test automation process.</span></li>
                <li style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="font-family: Candara; font-size: 11pt">Coordinates project planning efforts with other areas or cost centers affected by work unit projects.</span></li>
                <li style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="font-family: Candara; font-size: 11pt">Coordinates fail-over testing when new or major changes are made to an infrastructure.</span></li>
                <li style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="font-family: Candara; font-size: 11pt">Administers and controls test tools.</span></li>
                <li style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="font-family: Candara; font-size: 11pt">Creates, organizes and maintains the automated test script library.</span></li>
                <li style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="font-family: Candara; font-size: 11pt">May mentor or train other Automation Testers in processes, methods, tools and best practices.</span></li>
                <li style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="font-family: Candara; font-size: 11pt">Performs other related duties as assigned.</span></li>
            </ul>
